    "Testing and ValidationTesting and validation processes are critical to confirm that the system performs as intended under various conditions.",
    "The table II below compares the results of testing and validation between the baseline Kimi model and the enhanced Kimi model:TABLE II COMPARISON OF TESTING AND VALIDATION OUTCOMES BETWEEN BASELINE AND ENHANCED KIMI MODELS Testing Type Baseline Kimi Enhanced Kimi Unit Testing Success Rate 91% 98% Integration Success Rate 85% 95% System Testing Stability Occasional Failures Stable User Acceptance Satisfaction 73% 92% Regression Testing Pass Rate 81% 93% Continuous Feedback Moderate Issues Few IssuesThis table illustrates significant improvements in the testing and validation phases for the enhanced Kimi model.",
